Package fastmath.io

Class BigEndianInputStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.InputStream
      • java.io.FilterInputStream
        • java.io.DataInputStream
          • fastmath.io.BigEndianInputStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    UnsignedDataInput, Closeable, DataInput, AutoCloseable

    public class BigEndianInputStream
extends DataInputStream
implements UnsignedDataInput
    This class is a data input stream for little-endian data.

    LEInputStream tries very hard to be like java.io.DataInputStreamwhich describes:

      A data input stream lets an application read primitive Java data types from an underlying input stream in a machine-independent way. An application uses a data output stream to write data that can later be read by a data input stream.

    A little- endian data input stream lets an application read primitive Java data types from an underlying input stream in a little-endian way.

    Additionally, this class implements UnsignedDataInput. Java chooses not to provide any unsigned data types, so unsigned values are are cast to the next larger integral type (or class), thereby assuring that the values are never negative.

    Use LEOutputStreamto write unsigned little-endian data to a stream.

    See Also:
    DataInput, DataInputStream, DataOutputStream, LittleEndianOutputStream, UnsignedDataInput

        public long readUnsignedInt​()
                     throws IOException
        Returns int for the 32 bits read, treated as unsigned. Valid values range from 0 to 4294967295 (2 32 - 1), thus requiring a long return type to accurately represent the value. A negative value is never returned.
